Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips,
then pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over half the @mixed herbs{1/2%sachet}, then season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{0.25%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

While everything cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on
medium heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, butter beans,
remaining @mixed herbs{1/2%sachet}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the
sauce.

> See pantry for sugar and water amounts.

Stir to combine and bring to the boil, then lower the heat slightly and simmer
until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping
hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once roasted, add the sliced pepper to your sauce.

Stir the @creme fraiche{75%g} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{75%g}
through the sauce and bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the creamy butter beans and peppers.

Drizzle over the @fresh pesto{32%g} and sprinkle the remaining cheese on top to
finish. Enjoy!